name: SAY - Multiverse - CD Album
description:
Multiverse unveils SAY's new Pendle sound - The five piece provide a significant collection of songs at their alternative pop Pinnacle 

Whilst examining the magic that binds the universe together (!) their songs remain ever optimistic and uplifting. Peppered into Say's unique style are hints of the progressive attack of Mew, suggested inspirations from Brian Wilson, Flaming Lips as well as bits of a latter day Spiritualized in there too.

1. Mediarise
2. For You
3. The Disclosure Project
4. By The Window
5. The Flower of Life
6. Free The Animals
7. Quantum Galactica Major
8. Human Doing
9. Take Flight




Price Includes P&P to UK Only

name: POLITBURO - Line Of Wealth - CD Single
description:
"Politburo have (always) been great …playing the dark heart of rock & roll with deft and edgy skill. They manage to meld the Mancunian black heart expressway of Joy Division with the twisted molten punk of the Dead Kennedys - and that's a pretty damn brilliant combination" John Robb - Playlouder.com 

1. Line Of Wealth
2. Labour Day
3. Velocity
